        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Statement of authority given by Stephen F. Austin to sell Richmond, a slave.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><persName>Mr. Stephen F. Austin</persName> has this day given me authority to sell his
<persName>negro man Richmond</persName> for the Sum of Six hundred and fifty Dollars
(as the minimum price)&#8212; One hundred Dollars of the proceeds
of said <persName>negro </persName>is to be appropriated to pay said <persName>Austin</persName>'s note of this
date for that sum, the balance to be paid over to the order of said
<persName>S. F. Austin</persName>, or of <persName>Moses Austin</persName>, or of <persName>Joseph H. Hawkins Esquire
</persName>of <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>.</p>

<p>It is understood that should Said <persName>Austin </persName>hire out said <persName>Negro </persName>to
<persName>Hugh McGuffin</persName> he is to remain with <persName>McGuffin </persName>subject to be called
for whenever an opportunity offers to sell him&#8212;</p>

<p><placeName>Nachitoches </placeName><date when="1821-07-05">July 5, 1821</date></p>

<p><persName>A. Sampykao</persName></p>

        </div1>
    </body>
